{"title_page": "List of craters on Mars", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n__NOTOC__\n<!-- pie chart advanced -->\n{{Image frame\n |width = 210\n |align = right\n |pos = bottom\n |content =<div style=\"background-color: #F9F9F9; font-size: 0.85em; text-align: left; padding: 8px 0; margin: 0;\">\n {{#invoke:Chart\n  |pie chart\n  |radius = 100\n  |slices = \n    ( 1624 : lunar: #D6D6D6 : [[List of craters on the Moon]]) \n    ( 1092 : Martian: red) \n    ( 900 : Venerian : yellow : [[List of craters on Venus]]) \n    ( 397 : Mercurian : black : [[List of craters on Mercury]]) \n    ( 1198 : Others : white) \n  |units suffix = _craters\n  |percent = true\n  }}</div>\n |caption=Distribution of named [[Impact crater|craters]] in the [[Solar System]] as of 2017.\n}}\n\nThis is a '''list of craters on Mars'''. [[Impact crater]]s on [[Mars]] larger than 1&nbsp;km exist by the hundreds of thousands, but only about one thousand of them have names.<ref name=\"Gazetteer-Mars-Craterlist\" /> Names are assigned by the [[International Astronomical Union]] after petitioning by relevant scientists, and in general, only craters that have a significant research interest are given names. Martian craters are named after famous scientists and [[science fiction]] authors, or if less than 60&nbsp;km in diameter, after towns on [[Earth]]. Craters cannot be named for living people, and names for small craters are rarely intended to commemorate a specific town.<ref name=\"Gazetteer-Categories\" /> Latitude and longitude are given as planetographic coordinates with west longitude.\n\n== Catalog of named craters ==\n\nThe catalog is divided into three partial lists:\n* [[List of craters on Mars: A\u2013G]]\n* [[List of craters on Mars: H\u2013N]]\n* [[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z]]\n\nCraters on mars are created only by collisions with astroids.\n{{Compact ToC\n |side=no\n |name=List of craters on Mars\n |a=[[List of craters on Mars: A\u2013G#A|A]]\n |b=[[List of craters on Mars: A\u2013G#B|B]]\n |c=[[List of craters on Mars: A\u2013G#C|C]]\n |d=[[List of craters on Mars: A\u2013G#D|D]]\n |e=[[List of craters on Mars: A\u2013G#E|E]]\n |f=[[List of craters on Mars: A\u2013G#F|F]]\n |g=[[List of craters on Mars: A\u2013G#G|G]]\n |h=[[List of craters on Mars: H\u2013N#H|H]]\n |i=[[List of craters on Mars: H\u2013N#I|I]]\n |j=[[List of craters on Mars: H\u2013N#J|J]]\n |k=[[List of craters on Mars: H\u2013N#K|K]]\n |l=[[List of craters on Mars: H\u2013N#L|L]]\n |m=[[List of craters on Mars: H\u2013N#M|M]]\n |n=[[List of craters on Mars: H\u2013N#N|N]]\n |o=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#O|O]]\n |p=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#P|P]]\n |q=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#Q|Q]]\n |r=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#R|R]]\n |s=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#S|S]]\n |t=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#T|T]]\n |u=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#U|U]]\n |v=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#V|V]]\n |w=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#W|W]]\n |x=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#X|X]]\n |y=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#Y|Y]]\n |z=[[List of craters on Mars: O\u2013Z#Z|Z]]\n}}\n\n== Statistics ==\n\nAs of 2017, Martian craters account for 21% of all 5,211 named craters in the [[Solar System]]. Apart from the [[Moon]], no other body has as many named craters as Mars. Other, non-planetary bodies with numerous named craters include [[Callisto (moon)|Callisto]] ([[List of craters on Callisto|141]]), [[Ganymede (moon)|Ganymede]] ([[List of craters on Ganymede|131]]), [[Rhea (moon)|Rhea]] (128), [[4 Vesta|Vesta]] (90), [[Ceres (dwarf planet)|Ceres]] (90), [[Dione (moon)|Dione]] (73), [[Iapetus (moon)|Iapetus]] (58), [[Enceladus (moon)|Enceladus]] (53), [[Tethys (moon)|Tethys]] (50) and [[Europa (moon)|Europa]] ([[List of craters on Europa|41]]). For a full list, ''see [[List of craters in the Solar System]]''.\n\n=== Largest craters ===\n\nSome of the largest craters on Mars remain unnamed. Diameters differ depending on source data.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:10em\" | Crater{{efn|name=Column-Crater}}\n! style=\"width:10em\" | Coordinates\n! Diameter (km){{efn|name=Column-Diameter}}\n! [[Semi-major and semi-minor axes|Elliptical major axis]] (km)\n! [[Semi-major and semi-minor axes|Elliptical minor axis]] (km)\n! Rank by approx. area\n! Approval date\n! Named after\n! Refs\n|-\n| [[Huygens (crater)|Huygens]] || {{Coord|13.96|S|55.58|E|globe:mars_type:landmark|name=Huygens}} || 467.25 || 484.89 || 450.54 || 1 || 1973 || [[Christiaan Huygens]] || {{WGPSN|2596}}\n|-\n| [[Schiaparelli (Martian crater)|Schiaparelli]] || {{Coord|2.69|S|16.79|E|globe:mars_type:landmark|name=Schiaparelli}} || 458.52 (445.76) || 462.51 || 430.4 || 2 || 1973 || [[Giovanni Schiaparelli]] || {{WGPSN|5366}}\n|-\n| ''Unnamed'' <!-- id 02-000000 --> || {{Coord|38.1|N|167.15|W|globe:mars_type:landmark}} || 376.35 || 452.74 || 384.9 || 3 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2014\n|-\n| Greeley || {{Coord|36.63|S|3.19|E|globe:mars_type:landmark|name=Greeley}} || 457.45 (427.15) || 438.81 || 395.71 || 4 || 2015 || [[Ronald Greeley]] || {{WGPSN|15313}}\n|-\n| [[Cassini (Martian crater)|Cassini]] || {{Coord|22.59|N|32.11|E|globe:mars_type:landmark|name=Cassini}} || 408.23 || 411.45 || 402.42 || 5 || 1973 || [[Giovanni Domenico Cassini|Giovanni Cassini]] || {{WGPSN|1046}}\n|-\n| [[Antoniadi (Martian crater)|Antoniadi]] || {{Coord|21.59|N|60.84|E|globe:mars_type:landmark|name=Antoniadi}} || 400.95 || 417.04 || 389.68 || 6 || 1973 || [[E. M. Antoniadi|Eug\u00e8ne Michael Antoniadi]] || {{WGPSN|297}}\n|-\n| Dollfus || {{Coord|20.99|S|3.83|W|globe:mars_type:landmark|name=Dollfus}} || 363.08 (358.72) || 367.94 || 346.98 || 7 || 2013 || [[Audouin Dollfus]] || {{WGPSN|15168}}\n|-\n| ''Unnamed'' <!-- id 25-000000 --> || {{Coord|59.01|S|76.89|W|globe:mars_type:landmark}} || 341.1 || 391.76 || 325.82 || 8 || \u2013 || \u2013 || \u2014\n|-\n| [[Tikhonravov (crater)|Tikhonravov]] || {{Coord|12.92|